problem.markdown:
>>Which RNN architecture would you try first for a task with long sequences, where your models should run as fast as possible?<<

( ) Tanh RNN {{Tanh RNN will most likely not be able to deal with long sentences because of the gradient problems.}}
( ) LSTM {{LSTM is a good choice to handle long sequences but their complexity will probably result in high latency.}}
(x) GRU {{GRU would be the best choice for this task because they are complex enough to deal with long sentences and they have fewer equations than the LSTM. Because of this, they are usually faster.}}
